    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 186.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Baron
                                Gerolt</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 22, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, Secretary of State of the United States, has the honor
                            to acknowledge the receipt of the note of the 17th instant addressed to
                            him by the Baron Gerolt, the envoy extraordinary and minister
                            plenipotentiary of the North German Union, inclosing a copy of a
                            dispatch from the chancellor of his government of the 27th ultimo,
                            giving a statement of the negotiations which took place between himself
                            and Mr. Jules Favre.</p>
                <p>The undersigned begs the Baron Gerolt to accept a renewed assurance of
                            his highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
